This paper is about a benchmark for commonsense reasoning, which is a topic that falls under natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of neural language models, which falls under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of crowdsourcing and algorithmic bias reduction, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as well.
